Actress Annie Idibia has denied speculations of unfollowing her husband 2baba on Instragam. On Monday, several blogs and a news platform reported all was likely unwell with the couple, claiming the actress unfollowed her husband on Instagram. They alleged it was connected to the singer’s recent visit to US where he visited his first baby mama, Pero to see his three kids and shared several videos of bonding with them. Hours after sharing a cryptic post about family, Annie was reported to have unfollowed 2Baba on Instagram according to the blogs. But Annie debunked the report, noting it was all a case of an Instagram glitch.   Actor Kanayo hosts all white party for 60th birthday     Why I co-founded a dating restaurant for Lagosians –…     Italy show promoter yet to pay balance, Davido laments   Read Also: It’s time 2Baba gets vasectomy – Shade Ladipo She hailed bloggers for their immense love for bad news and warned them to desist from frightening the fans. According to the mother of two: “Jesu ooo. Na so una like bad news tire! Na wa o. Simple Instagram glitch, una don create story. Nigerian bloggers, I hail! “Make una no dey let innocent lovers of a guy and I mind jump o! #unwashthebrainwashed biko ooo. “Serious Trash. Lol! Mbok oooo. Ahhhh ! Bloggers y’all r real vibes mannnnnnn. I salute Una ooo. But hey #annieidibiatrending everywhere already lol.”